'31:31': [
{sup:"1a", word:"new", vrefs:"Jer. 32:40; Ezek. 37:26; Matt. 26:28; Luke 22:20; 1&nbsp;Cor. 11:25; 2&nbsp;Cor. 3:6; Heb. 8:8-12; 10:16-17", lines:["Jeremiah&rsquo;s prophecy in vv. {Jer31:31|31}-{Jer31:34|34} concerning the new covenant was quoted by the apostle Paul in {Heb8:8|Heb. 8:8}-{Heb8:12|12} and was applied to the New Testament believers. Thus, the new covenant with its privileges and blessings is for the New Testament believers to enjoy in the present age. Israel&rsquo;s participation in the new covenant will be in the millennium, in the coming age of restoration ({Mat19:28|Matt. 19:28}), in which Christ will be Israel&rsquo;s righteousness, redemption, and life and will be exalted to be their centrality and universality. Eventually, through the new covenant God will make the believers and Israel a new creation ({2Co5:17|2&nbsp;Cor. 5:17}; {Gal6:15|Gal. 6:15}), which will ultimately consummate in the New Jerusalem in the new heaven and new earth for eternity ({Rev21:1|Rev. 21:1}-{Rev21:3|3})."]},
],
